 Colombia’s midfielder James Rodriguez reacts as he leaves the pitch after getting injured during the Russia 2018 World Cup Group H football match between Senegal and Colombia at the Samara Arena in Samara on June 28, 2018. / AFP PHOTO / Luis Acosta /  James, who was top scorer at the 2014 World Cup with six goals, limped off in the first half of Colombia’s last group game against Senegal on Thursday. An MRI scan showed he has “minor bruising without any tear in the muscle fibres”, the Colombian football federation said. Colombia face England at Moscow’s Spartak Stadium on Tuesday.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .